<h5 id="what-do-you-do-when-an-application-you-have-just-downloaded-asks-you-for-your-phone-number">WHAT DO YOU DO WHEN AN APPLICATION YOU HAVE JUST DOWNLOADED ASKS YOU FOR YOUR PHONE NUMBER?</h5>

<blockquote>
  <p>There are these apps that you know, for sure that they need it, you always understand the logic behind it. Otherwise I don’t provide it, but if it’s a social media app like Twitter or Instagram, I know for a fact they will need it to generate my contacts and make me communicate with people.</p>

  <p>That’s why they need my contact information. If it is a dictionary, come on. Why do you need my names and things to give me a dictionary?</p>
</blockquote>

<h5 id="what-would-you-do-if-your-google-cloud-runs-out-of-space">WHAT WOULD YOU DO IF YOUR GOOGLE CLOUD RUNS OUT OF SPACE?</h5>

<blockquote>
  <p>That’s hasn’t reached there yet. I can figure out something when that happens.</p>

  <p>I would go back and delete some things or transfer some of my things to some of the other accounts. You know, there are so many other ways you can, can have them online.</p>

  <p>Someone can even have 2 Gmails or use Dropbox.</p>
</blockquote>
